    <h1>About Lionel Messi</h1>

    <img src="https://resize.indiatvnews.com/en/resize/newbucket/1200_-/2025/08/untitled-design-2025-08-29t105052-1756444869.webp" alt="Lionel Messi">

    <p>
        <strong>Lionel Messi</strong> is a professional footballer from <em>Argentina</em>, widely regarded as one of the greatest players of all time. 
        He currently plays for <span class="highlight">Inter Miami</span> in Major League Soccer (MLS) and the Argentina national team.
    </p>

    <h2>Early Life</h2>
    <p>
        Messi was born on June 24, 1987, in Rosario, Argentina. From a young age, he showed exceptional talent in football and joined the youth system of Newell's Old Boys. At age 13, he moved to Spain to join <strong>FC Barcelona</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>Career Achievements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>7-time Ballon d'Or winner</li>
        <li>4-time UEFA Champions League winner with Barcelona</li>
        <li>2022 FIFA World Cup Champion with Argentina</li>
        <li>All-time top scorer for Barcelona</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Fun Facts</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Heâ€™s known for his left-footed dribbling and amazing vision on the field.</li>
        <li>Messi holds the record for most goals in a calendar year (91 in 2012).</li>
        <li>He is a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
        For more about Messi, visit his <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lionel_Messi" target="_blank">Wikipedia page</a>.
    </p>

